<div id="node-136" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/136" title="Article: Message-Driven POJOs">Article: Message-Driven POJOs</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Colin Sampaleanu on Fri, 2005-07-15 13:42        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_6 first last active"><a href="/presentations" rel="tag" title="A link to a technical article about Spring" class="active">Technical Article</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p><a target="_self" href="http://jroller.com/page/habuma/20050715#message_driven_pojos">Message-Driven POJOs</a>
is a detailed blog entry by Craig Walls which explores the
Spring-based, JMS, 'message-driven POJOs' available as part of the
ActiveMQ codebase. This code effectively tries to replicate EJB MDB
functionality, in plain java objects configured via Spring.</p><p>Update 2005-7-22: part 2, <a href="http://jroller.com/page/habuma?entry=message_driven_pojos_2_the" target="_self">Message-driven POJOs revisited</a>, is now available.&nbsp;</p><p>Colin's
note: while this code is part of the ActiveMQ codebase, when talking to
James Strachan in mid-May 2005 about it, James mentioned that while the
code has been used and tested mostly with ActiveMQ, there is nothing
inherently ActiveMQ-specific about it. Usage with other JMS servers
will at a minimum require testing and verification.<br />
</p>  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_comments first last"><a href="/node/136#comments" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">1 comment</a></li>
</ul>
</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
<div id="node-135" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/135" title="Article in French: M2VC, un moteur MVC pour des applications GUI Java">Article in French: M2VC, un moteur MVC pour des applications GUI Java</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Colin Sampaleanu on Fri, 2005-07-15 13:30        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_6 first last active"><a href="/presentations" rel="tag" title="A link to a technical article about Spring" class="active">Technical Article</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p><a target="_self" href="http://tahe.developpez.com/java/m2vc/">M2VC, un moteur MVC pour des applications GUI Java</a>
is a comprehensive (37 page) article in French, by Serge Tahé. It
details a web MVC style framework built on Swing, backed by Spring for
object management and general IoC.</p>  </div>

