      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/129" title="Article: Spring by Example - Part 1">Article: Spring by Example - Part 1</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Keith Donald on Fri, 2005-07-08 15:56        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_6 first last active"><a href="/presentations" rel="tag" title="A link to a technical article about Spring" class="active">Technical Article</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>In this first part of a multi-part series, Keith Donald looks at the process of building a slice of a business system &quot;the Spring way&quot;, noting how to achieve several important design goals that enable you to write cleaner, more testable code.&nbsp; Read <a href="http://www.jroller.com/page/kdonald" target="_self">Spring by Example</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_comments first last"><a href="/node/129#comments" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">1 comment</a></li>
</ul>
